<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,485,151,210]" box="[151,422,186,210]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
(
<figureCitation box="[158,259,186,210]" captionStart="PLATE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,233,1909,1932]" captionTargetBox="[162,1420,212,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-97@6.[151,1435,195,1885]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="PLATE 1. A–I. Teruliini, dorsal habitus. (A) Freytagolidia ligula, sp. nov., holotype; (B) Neodocalidia connectiva sp. nov., holotype; (C) Baluba sharkeyi, sp. nov., holotype; (D) Bolidiana robusta, sp. nov., holotype; (E) Bolidiana trisetacea, sp. nov., holotype; (F) Bolidiana elongata, sp. nov., holotype; (G) Harasupia lyrata, sp. nov., holotype; (H) Hastalidia acinaca, sp. nov., holotype; (I) Jalorpa constricta, sp. nov., holotype." pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Plate 1H</figureCitation>
), 
<figureCitation box="[281,414,186,210]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–63" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1879,1902]" captionTargetBox="[193,1364,198,1829]" captionTargetId="figure-62@19.[181,1369,160,1839]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 57–63. Hastalidia acinaca, sp. nov. (57) pygofer, lateral view; (58) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (59) right style, dorsal view; (60) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (61) aedeagus, ventral view; (62) connective, dorsal view; (63) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Figs. 57–63</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,258,930]" box="[151,693,258,283]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,243,259,283]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" reason="1">Length.</emphasis>
Male 6.20–6.80 mm., female unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,258,930]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,416,295,319]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" reason="1">External morphology.</emphasis>
Medium sized, robust species. General color fuscous with 2 broad, flavous, transverse bands on forewings, apex flavous to fuscous, face fuscous (
<figureCitation box="[841,945,330,354]" captionStart="PLATE 1" captionStartId="6.[151,233,1909,1932]" captionTargetBox="[162,1420,212,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-97@6.[151,1435,195,1885]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="PLATE 1. A–I. Teruliini, dorsal habitus. (A) Freytagolidia ligula, sp. nov., holotype; (B) Neodocalidia connectiva sp. nov., holotype; (C) Baluba sharkeyi, sp. nov., holotype; (D) Bolidiana robusta, sp. nov., holotype; (E) Bolidiana trisetacea, sp. nov., holotype; (F) Bolidiana elongata, sp. nov., holotype; (G) Harasupia lyrata, sp. nov., holotype; (H) Hastalidia acinaca, sp. nov., holotype; (I) Jalorpa constricta, sp. nov., holotype." pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Plate 1H</figureCitation>
). Head large, nearly as wide as pronotum, anterior margin rounded; crown broad, wider than width of eyes, anterior margin slightly produce, disk depressed; eyes large, somewhat globular; pronotum large, length greater than median length of crown, inflated; mesonotum large, length greater than median length of pronotum; forewings long, broad, 3 anteapical cells present, outer one closed; clypellus moderately long, broad, with prominent median longitudinal carina; clypellus narrow, lateral margins converging apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1436,258,930]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,373,546,571]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" reason="1">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view narrow, with prominent, stout caudodorsal process, (
<figureCitation box="[1225,1308,546,570]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–63" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1879,1902]" captionTargetBox="[193,1364,198,1829]" captionTargetId="figure-62@19.[181,1369,160,1839]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 57–63. Hastalidia acinaca, sp. nov. (57) pygofer, lateral view; (58) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (59) right style, dorsal view; (60) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (61) aedeagus, ventral view; (62) connective, dorsal view; (63) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
); right subgenital plate long, narrow, broadly curved, glabrous (
<figureCitation box="[758,843,582,606]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–63" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1879,1902]" captionTargetBox="[193,1364,198,1829]" captionTargetId="figure-62@19.[181,1369,160,1839]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 57–63. Hastalidia acinaca, sp. nov. (57) pygofer, lateral view; (58) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (59) right style, dorsal view; (60) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (61) aedeagus, ventral view; (62) connective, dorsal view; (63) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
); style long, longer than aedeagus, robust (
<figureCitation box="[1337,1423,582,606]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–63" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1879,1902]" captionTargetBox="[193,1364,198,1829]" captionTargetId="figure-62@19.[181,1369,160,1839]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 57–63. Hastalidia acinaca, sp. nov. (57) pygofer, lateral view; (58) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (59) right style, dorsal view; (60) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (61) aedeagus, ventral view; (62) connective, dorsal view; (63) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
); aedeagus short, tubular with narrow, circular apex (
<figureCitation box="[730,825,618,642]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–63" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1879,1902]" captionTargetBox="[193,1364,198,1829]" captionTargetId="figure-62@19.[181,1369,160,1839]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 57–63. Hastalidia acinaca, sp. nov. (57) pygofer, lateral view; (58) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (59) right style, dorsal view; (60) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (61) aedeagus, ventral view; (62) connective, dorsal view; (63) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Figs. 60</figureCitation>
); connective Y-shaped, stem short, without membrane medially (
<figureCitation box="[266,352,654,678]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–63" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1879,1902]" captionTargetBox="[193,1364,198,1829]" captionTargetId="figure-62@19.[181,1369,160,1839]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 57–63. Hastalidia acinaca, sp. nov. (57) pygofer, lateral view; (58) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (59) right style, dorsal view; (60) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (61) aedeagus, ventral view; (62) connective, dorsal view; (63) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Fig. 61</figureCitation>
); dorsal connective relatively short, broad in lateral view, very narrow, broad basally in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[220,357,690,714]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–63" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1879,1902]" captionTargetBox="[193,1364,198,1829]" captionTargetId="figure-62@19.[181,1369,160,1839]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 57–63. Hastalidia acinaca, sp. nov. (57) pygofer, lateral view; (58) right subgenital plate, ventral view; (59) right style, dorsal view; (60) aedeagus and dorsal connective, lateral view; (61) aedeagus, ventral view; (62) connective, dorsal view; (63) dorsal connective, dorsal view." pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Figs. 61, 63</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
